01:58:43,691 --> 01:58:45,942
Let's just wrap it up.

2022
01:58:45,943 --> 01:58:48,736
- Come in and we'll tell Mom.
- I don't want to see her.

2023
01:58:48,737 --> 01:58:50,571
- Come on.
- I don't want to see her.

2024
01:58:50,572 --> 01:58:53,116
Don't bother me, will ya?

2025
01:58:53,117 --> 01:58:55,743
Dad, what do you mean?
You don't want to see her?

2026
01:58:55,744 --> 01:58:59,373
Pop, you don't want them
calling you yellow, do you?

2027
01:58:59,456 --> 01:59:03,585
Dad, it's not your fault.
It's me. I'm a bum.

2028
01:59:03,669 --> 01:59:06,146
Now, come on inside.

2029
01:59:06,880 --> 01:59:10,233
Dad, did you hear what I said to you?

2030
01:59:16,723 --> 01:59:18,992
Did you plant, dear?

2031
01:59:20,436 --> 01:59:23,038
All right, Mom.

2032
01:59:24,189 --> 01:59:27,443
We had it out.
I'm going and I'm not writing anymore.

2033
01:59:27,526 --> 01:59:29,485
I think it's best, Willy.

2034
01:59:29,486 --> 01:59:32,573
There's no use drawing it out.
You two will never get along.

2035
01:59:32,656 --> 01:59:35,617
If people ask where I am,
what I'm doing, you don't know or care.

2036
01:59:35,701 --> 01:59:39,830
That way it'll be off your mind
and you can start brightening up again.

2037
01:59:39,913 --> 01:59:42,474
All right?

2038
01:59:48,213 --> 01:59:51,024
That... That clears it, then, huh?

2039
02:00:07,024 --> 02:00:11,069
- You gonna wish me luck, scout?
- Shake his hand, Willy.

2040
02:00:11,153 --> 02:00:13,404
What do you say?

2041
02:00:13,405 --> 02:00:16,825
There's no necessity to mention...
He put his arm...!

2042
02:00:16,909 --> 02:00:20,621
Dad, you're never gonna see what I am,
so what's the use of arguing?

2043
02:00:20,704 --> 02:00:24,166
If I strike oil I'll send you a cheque.
Meantime, forget I'm alive.

2044
02:00:24,249 --> 02:00:26,250
Spite, see?

2045
02:00:26,251 --> 02:00:29,562
- Shake hands, Dad.
- Not my hand.

2046
02:00:34,218 --> 02:00:36,277
Dad?

2047
02:00:36,678 --> 02:00:40,641
- I was hoping not to go this way.
- This is the way you're going. Bye.

2048
02:00:44,394 --> 02:00:48,231
May you rot in hell
if you leave this house!

2049
02:00:48,315 --> 02:00:50,942
Exactly what is it
that you want from me?

2050
02:00:50,943 --> 02:00:54,780
I want you to know on the train,
in the mountains, in the valleys,

2051
02:00:54,863 --> 02:00:58,367
wherever you go,
that you cut down your life for spite!

2052
02:00:58,450 --> 02:01:01,594
- No, no!
- Spite!

2053
02:01:06,458 --> 02:01:10,504
When you are rotting somewhere
beside a railroad track, remember.

2054
02:01:10,587 --> 02:01:13,422
- Don't you blame it on me.
- I'm not blaming you.

2055
02:01:13,423 --> 02:01:15,967
I'm not taking the rap for this, hear?

2056
02:01:15,968 --> 02:01:19,054
- That's what I'm telling you.
- You're putting a knife in me.

2057
02:01:19,137 --> 02:01:21,889
Don't think I don't know
what you're doing.

2058
02:01:21,890 --> 02:01:24,600
All right, phoney.
Leave it there. Don't move it.

2059
02:01:24,601 --> 02:01:26,811
- What is that?
- You know damn well.

2060
02:01:26,812 --> 02:01:29,146
- I never saw that.
- You saw it, all right.

2061
02:01:29,147 --> 02:01:32,943
Mice didn't bring it into the cellar.
Is that supposed to make you a hero?

2062
02:01:33,026 --> 02:01:36,488
That supposed to make me sorry for you?
There will be no pity for you.

2063
02:01:36,571 --> 02:01:38,572
- Hear that? No pity.
- Hear the spite?

2064
02:01:38,573 --> 02:01:41,158
You're gonna get the truth,
what you are, what I am.

2065
02:01:41,159 --> 02:01:42,868
- Spite!
- Cut it out!

2066
02:01:42,869 --> 02:01:45,831
The man don't know who we are.
The man is gonna know.

2067
02:01:46,707 --> 02:01:49,626
We never told the truth
for ten minutes in this house.

2068
02:01:49,710 --> 02:01:52,586
- We always told truth.
- Are you the assistant buyer?

2069
02:01:52,587 --> 02:01:55,297
You're one of
the two assistants to the assistant.

2070
02:01:55,298 --> 02:01:57,967
- I'm practically...
- You are practically full of it.

2071
02:01:57,968 --> 02:02:00,261
- We all are. I'm through with it.
- Yeah.

2072
02:02:00,262 --> 02:02:03,197
- Hear this, Willy. This is me.
- I know you.

2073
02:02:03,432 --> 02:02:06,308
Do you know why I had no
address for three months?

2074
02:02:06,309 --> 02:02:09,019
I stole a suit in Kansas City
and I was in gaol.

2075
02:02:09,020 --> 02:02:12,357
- I suppose it's my fault.
- Stop crying, I'm through with it!

2076
02:02:12,441 --> 02:02:15,569
I stole myself
out of every good job since high school.

2077
02:02:15,652 --> 02:02:17,069
Whose fault is that?

2078
02:02:17,070 --> 02:02:20,407
I could never get anywhere
'cause you blew me so full of hot air

2079
02:02:20,532 --> 02:02:23,367
that I could never stand
taking orders from anybody.

2080
02:02:23,368 --> 02:02:25,661
- I hear that.
- Stop it!

2081
02:02:25,662 --> 02:02:28,498
I had to be boss big shot
in two weeks and I'm through.

2082
02:02:28,582 --> 02:02:31,000
- Then hang yourself for spite!
- No! No!

2083
02:02:31,001 --> 02:02:34,796
No, nobody is hanging himself, Willy.

2084
02:02:37,924 --> 02:02:42,471
I ran down 11 flights with a pen
in my hand today.

2085
02:02:42,554 --> 02:02:44,889
And suddenly I stopped.
Do you hear me?

2086
02:02:44,890 --> 02:02:48,226
In the middle of that office building...
Do you hear this?

2087
02:02:48,310 --> 02:02:50,436
I stopped...

2088
02:02:50,437 --> 02:02:54,483
...in the middle of the building
and I saw the sky!

2089
02:02:54,566 --> 02:03:00,447
And I... I... I saw the things
that I love in this world.

2090
02:03:00,572 --> 02:03:04,017
The work and the food

2091
02:03:04,201 --> 02:03:07,037
and the time to sit and smoke.

2092
02:03:07,120 --> 02:03:11,458
I looked at that pen in my hand and
I said, "What am I grabbing this for?

2093
02:03:11,541 --> 02:03:14,251
Why am I trying to become
what I don't want to be?

2094
02:03:14,252 --> 02:03:15,920
What am I doing in an office?

2095
02:03:15,921 --> 02:03:19,049
Making a contemptuous begging
fool of myself,

2096
02:03:19,132 --> 02:03:21,884
when all that I want
is out there waiting for me?"

2097
02:03:21,885 --> 02:03:25,222
The minute I say it, I know who I am.
Why can't I say that, Willy?

2098
02:03:25,305 --> 02:03:27,306
The door to your life is wide open!

2099
02:03:27,307 --> 02:03:29,808
Pop, I am a dime a dozen and so are you.

2100
02:03:29,809 --> 02:03:32,436
I am not a dime a dozen!

2101
02:03:32,437 --> 02:03:35,398
I am Willy Loman and you are Biff Loman!

2102
02:03:35,482 --> 02:03:39,285
I am not the leader of men, Willy!
And neither are you!

2103
02:03:39,486 --> 02:03:42,948
You were never anything
but a hard-working drummer

2104
02:03:43,073 --> 02:03:45,908
who landed in the ashcan
like all the rest of them.

2105
02:03:45,909 --> 02:03:48,535
I am one dollar an hour, Willy!

2106
02:03:48,536 --> 02:03:52,249
I am not bringing home
any prizes anymore,

2107
02:03:52,332 --> 02:03:54,500
and you're gonna stop waiting for me!

2108
02:03:54,501 --> 02:03:58,338
- You vengeful, spiteful mutt!
- Yeah, Pop!

2109
02:03:58,421 --> 02:04:01,383
Pop, I'm nothing.

2110
02:04:01,466 --> 02:04:04,552
I'm nothing, Pop.
Can't you understand that?

2111
02:04:04,636 --> 02:04:06,971
There's no spite in it anymore.

2112
02:04:06,972 --> 02:04:09,865
I'm just what I am, that's all.

2113
02:04:11,518 --> 02:04:14,854
What are you doing?
Aw, what are you doing?

2114
02:04:19,693 --> 02:04:22,946
- Why is he crying?
- Dad...

2115
02:04:24,155 --> 02:04:26,882
Will you let me go, for God's sake?

2116
02:04:27,826 --> 02:04:33,164
Will you take that phoney dream
and burn it before something happens?

2117
02:05:12,537 --> 02:05:15,431
I'll go in the morning.

2118
02:05:19,127 --> 02:05:21,437
Put him to bed.

2119
02:05:28,511 --> 02:05:32,557
Isn't that...
Isn't that remarkable?

2120
02:05:33,641 --> 02:05:36,478
Biff, he...

2121
02:05:38,104 --> 02:05:40,998
He likes me.

2122
02:05:41,274 --> 02:05:44,944
- He loves you, Willy.
- Always did, Pop.

2123
02:05:45,028 --> 02:05:47,696
Aw, Biff, he...

2124
02:05:47,697 --> 02:05:50,466
He cried. He cried to me.

2125
02:05:50,909 --> 02:05:54,537
Aw, that boy.
That boy, he's going to be magnificent.

2126
02:05:55,663 --> 02:05:58,457
Yes, outstanding,
with 20,000 behind him.

2127
02:05:58,458 --> 02:06:01,001
Come to bed, Willy.
It's all settled now.

2128
02:06:01,002 --> 02:06:04,422
Oh, yes, we'll sleep.
Come on, let's go to sleep.

2129
02:06:04,547 --> 02:06:07,132
It takes a great man
to crack thejungle.

2130
02:06:07,133 --> 02:06:10,470
I'm getting married.
Don't forget. I'm changing everything.

2131
02:06:10,553 --> 02:06:13,515
I'm gonna run that department
before the year is up.

2132
02:06:13,598 --> 02:06:16,183
Thejungle is dark
but full of diamonds.

2133
02:06:16,184 --> 02:06:19,687
Be good. You're both good boys.
Just act that way, that's all.

2134
02:06:21,189 --> 02:06:23,699
- Night, Pop.
- Night, boy.

2135
02:06:24,567 --> 02:06:28,111
- Come, dear. -S hh. One must
go in to fetch a diamond out.

2136
02:06:28,112 --> 02:06:30,822
I just want to get settled down
for a little while.

2137
02:06:30,823 --> 02:06:33,952
- I want you upstairs.
- A few minutes. I couldn't sleep now.

2138
02:06:34,077 --> 02:06:36,955
- Go. You look awful tired.
- Not like an appointment.

2139
02:06:37,038 --> 02:06:40,083
- A diamond is rough and hard to touch.
- I'll be right up.

2140
02:06:40,208 --> 02:06:43,044
- I think it's the only way.
- Sure, it's the best thing.

2141
02:06:43,127 --> 02:06:47,991
Best thing. The only way.
Everything is gonna be...

2142
02:06:48,174 --> 02:06:51,151
Aw, go on, kid. Get to bed.

2143
02:06:52,128 --> 02:06:56,591
- You look so tired. - Now, you
come right up. - Two minutes.

2144
02:07:05,141 --> 02:07:08,227
Loves me. Always loved me.
Isn't that a remarkable thing?

2145
02:07:08,311 --> 02:07:12,648
- Ben, he'll worship me for it.
- It's dark there.

2146
02:07:12,732 --> 02:07:14,524
But full of diamonds, Willy.

2147
02:07:14,525 --> 02:07:18,321
Can you imagine that magnificence
with $20,000 in his pocket?

2148
02:07:18,404 --> 02:07:20,530
Willy, come up.

2149
02:07:20,531 --> 02:07:23,283
Yes, yes, coming, coming!

2150
02:07:23,384 --> 02:07:26,345
It's very smart,
you realise, don't you, sweetheart?

2151
02:07:26,429 --> 02:07:28,221
Even Ben sees it.

2152
02:07:28,222 --> 02:07:30,741
I gotta go, baby.

2153
02:07:34,395 --> 02:07:36,580
Bye-bye.

2154
02:07:37,189 --> 02:07:40,026
When the mail comes
he'll be ahead of Bernard again.

2155
02:07:40,109 --> 02:07:44,654
- A perfect proposition all around.
- Did you see how he cried to me?

2156
02:07:44,655 --> 02:07:48,683
- Aw, I could kiss him, Ben.
- Time, William, time.

2157
02:07:48,784 --> 02:07:52,872
Ben, I always knew one way or another
we were gonna make it, Biff and I.

2158
02:07:52,955 --> 02:07:56,250
Boat! We'll be late.

2159
02:07:57,710 --> 02:08:02,965
Now, when you kick off,
I want a 70 yard boot.

2160
02:08:03,049 --> 02:08:06,594
And get right down the field
under the ball.

2161
02:08:06,677 --> 02:08:10,014
And when you hit,
hit low and hit hard,

2162
02:08:10,139 --> 02:08:12,515
because it's important, boy.

2163
02:08:12,516 --> 02:08:16,645
There's all kinds of
important people in the stands.

2164
02:08:17,521 --> 02:08:20,248
The first thing that you know...

2165
02:08:20,608 --> 02:08:22,108
Willy?

2166
02:08:22,109 --> 02:08:25,029
- Ben? Ben, where do I...?
- Willy?

2167
02:08:25,112 --> 02:08:29,200
- Ben! Ben!
- Willy!

2168
02:08:30,284 --> 02:08:31,993
Shh. Shh.

2169
02:08:31,994 --> 02:08:34,746
Shh! Shh!

2170
02:08:34,747 --> 02:08:37,808
- Willy, please come up.
- Oh.

2171
02:08:39,752 --> 02:08:41,978
- Willy!
- Shh!

2172
02:08:46,425 --> 02:08:48,485
Willy?

2173
02:08:51,013 --> 02:08:54,516
- Pop?
- Willy, answer me!

2174
02:08:54,517 --> 02:08:57,828
Willy!

2175
02:08:59,288 --> 02:09:03,209
- Willy!
- Pop! No!

2176
02:09:04,084 --> 02:09:06,770
- No!
- No!

2177
02:09:10,758 --> 02:09:14,929
It's getting dark, Linda.

2178
02:09:16,472 --> 02:09:20,768
How about it, Ma? Better get
some rest. They'll be closing the gates.

2179
02:09:20,893 --> 02:09:23,938
He had no right to do that.
There was no necessity.

2180
02:09:24,021 --> 02:09:26,941
- We would have helped him.
- Come on.

2181
02:09:27,024 --> 02:09:31,235
- Why didn't anybody come?
- It was a very nice funeral.

2182
02:09:31,236 --> 02:09:34,448
Where were the people he knew?
Maybe they blame him.

2183
02:09:34,531 --> 02:09:37,910
It's a rough world, Linda.
They wouldn't blame him.

2184
02:09:37,993 --> 02:09:42,990
I can't understand it.
First time in just about 35 years

2185
02:09:43,374 --> 02:09:46,919
we were almost free and clear.

2186
02:09:48,170 --> 02:09:51,356
He only needed a little salary.

2187
02:09:51,423 --> 02:09:54,385
He was even finished with the dentist.

2188
02:09:54,468 --> 02:09:57,471
No man only needs a little salary.

2189
02:09:59,056 --> 02:10:01,015
I can't understand it.

2190
02:10:01,016 --> 02:10:06,480
There were a lot of nice days when he'd
come home from a trip or on Sundays,

2191
02:10:06,563 --> 02:10:09,942
making the stoop,
finishing the cellar

2192
02:10:10,025 --> 02:10:14,196
when he built the extra bathroom
and put up the garage.

2193
02:10:15,614 --> 02:10:19,201
You know, Charley, I think there was
more of him in that front stoop

2194
02:10:19,284 --> 02:10:21,619
than in all the sales he ever made.

2195
02:10:21,620 --> 02:10:25,916
Yep. He was a happy man
with a bunch of cement.

2196
02:10:25,999 --> 02:10:28,835
He was wonderful with his hands.

2197
02:10:28,836 --> 02:10:32,089
He had the wrong dreams.
AII, all wrong.

2198
02:10:32,172 --> 02:10:35,433
Don't say that.
The man didn't know who he was.

2199
02:10:35,634 --> 02:10:38,511
Nobody dast blame this man.

2200
02:10:38,512 --> 02:10:40,905
You don't understand.

2201
02:10:41,306 --> 02:10:44,242
Willy was a salesman.

2202
02:10:44,810 --> 02:10:47,646
For a salesman,
there is no rock bottom to the life.

2203
02:10:47,729 --> 02:10:49,605
He don't put a bolt to a nut,

2204
02:10:49,606 --> 02:10:52,400
he don't tell you the law,
don't give you medicine.

2205
02:10:52,401 --> 02:10:55,237
He's a man way out there in the blue,

2206
02:10:56,530 --> 02:10:59,382
riding on a smile and a shoeshine.

2207
02:10:59,867 --> 02:11:04,545
When they start not smiling back,
that's an earthquake.

2208
02:11:04,746 --> 02:11:08,500
You get yourself a couple of spots
on your hat and you're finished.

2209
02:11:10,294 --> 02:11:13,354
Nobody dast blame this man.

2210
02:11:13,714 --> 02:11:17,242
A salesman has got to dream, boy.
Comes with the territory.

2211
02:11:17,426 --> 02:11:21,345
- The man didn't know who he was.
- Don't say that!

2212
02:11:21,346 --> 02:11:24,365
Why don't you come with me, Happy?

2213
02:11:24,975 --> 02:11:27,452
I'm not licked that easily.

2214
02:11:27,811 --> 02:11:31,064
I'm staying right in the city
and I'm gonna beat this racquet.

2215
02:11:32,816 --> 02:11:35,485
- Loman brothers.
- I know who I am, kid.

2216
02:11:35,486 --> 02:11:38,237
All right, boy,
I'm gonna show you and everybody

2217
02:11:38,238 --> 02:11:41,700
that Willy Loman did not die in vain.
He had a good dream.

2218
02:11:41,783 --> 02:11:45,078
It's the only dream you can have,
to come out number one man.

2219
02:11:45,162 --> 02:11:48,840
He fought it out here and this is where
I'm gonna win it for him.

2220
02:11:51,376 --> 02:11:54,103
Oh, I'll be with you in just a minute.

2221
02:11:54,421 --> 02:11:57,181
You go on, Charley.

2222
02:11:57,466 --> 02:12:00,109
Just... just a minute.

2223
02:12:04,473 --> 02:12:07,742
I never had a chance to say good-bye.

2224
02:12:16,944 --> 02:12:19,603
Help me, Willy.

2225
02:12:19,821 --> 02:12:22,298
I can't cry.

2226
02:12:22,908 --> 02:12:27,829
Seems to me you're just away on
another trip and I keep expecting you.

2227
02:12:30,290 --> 02:12:32,900
Why did you do it?

2228
02:12:34,294 --> 02:12:37,172
I search and I search,

2229
02:12:38,298 --> 02:12:41,134
and I search,

2230
02:12:42,469 --> 02:12:47,432
and I can't understand it, Willy.

2231
02:12:50,644 --> 02:12:54,247
I made the last payment
on the house today.

2232
02:12:55,774 --> 02:12:58,167
Today!

2233
02:13:05,409 --> 02:13:08,645
And there'll be nobody home.

2234
02:13:10,789 --> 02:13:14,083
We're free and clear.

2235
02:13:18,088 --> 02:13:20,598
We're free.

2236
02:13:21,383 --> 02:13:23,901
We're free.

2237
02:13:28,598 --> 02:13:31,326
We're free.

